
Some MM code for GPU. Compile.matmul.sh creates 4 different exe
* mm.matmul.serial.x: a CPU version of matmul
* mm.matmul.validation.x: a CPU version of matmul with validation of the result
* mm.matmul.gpu.x: a GPU version of matmul 
* mm.matmul.gpu.validation.x: a GPU version of matmul with result validation

CAVEAT: 
with leonardo use nvhpc 25.4, 24.9 doesn't work.....
